resources.string: This rabbit comes from Ankara, Turkey. The Angora rabbit became known to the public outside Turkey after in 1723, this rabbit was introduced to France by British sailors.
The Dutch rabbit, also known as the Dutch rabbit, is unique in its fur. This rabbit from the Netherlands is known for its diversity of coat colors, although its fur is quite short.
The natherland dwarf rabbit, this rabbit is tiny, weighing only 490 grams to 1.1 kilograms and can survive to the age of 10-12 years if properly cared for

Holland lop belongs to the category of dwarf rabbit. Because, it weighs only 900 grams to 1.8 kilograms, says the Pet Helpful page. These rabbits can be recognized by their drooping ears, round head, and thick hair.
Lovebirds Most lovebird species come from Africa and the rest from Madagascar. The name of this love bird is observed from the Lovebird characters who are often close together and love each other.
The white starling comes from Indonesia. The White Starling is a bird that belongs to the Sturnidae family.
The red vector canary bird comes from Indonesia. This bird has a gacor chirp and beautiful feathers
This bird from Southeast Irian is longer than the Little Yellow, which is 34 cm.

Clown fish are tropical reef fish that live in warm waters on coral reefs with a depth of less than 50 cm and clear water
This fish causes poisoning if eaten by humans, but is much sought after as an ornamental fish.
Firefish are popular reef aquarium fish due to their resistance to disease. This fish comes from the Philippines
